honeywell.printer.configuration.ez

Class BluetoothConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterData
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterState
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.BluetoothConfiguration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class BluetoothConfiguration
extends PrinterState
    This class handles the data from an {BL?} query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    ADevice's authentication setting.
    ADUnique MAC address of the Bluetooth device.
    BDevice's bondable setting
    CDevice's connectable setting
    CLDevice class for the Bluetooth device.
    DDevice's discoverability setting
    EDevice's encryption setting.
    FFriendly name of the Bluetooth device.
    IHow long before the device will automatically disconnect.
    PDevice's passkey configuration.
    PRBluetooth profiles supported.
    PWRIs the Bluetooth module powered.
    SNService name of the Bluetooth device.
    WHow long is the watchdog period for Bluetooth
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • BluetoothConfiguration

        public BluetoothConfiguration(ConnectionBase connection)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        connection - connection to printer
